# Specific Contributions to Community Changes

__s3c__ (_Specific Contributions to Community Changes_) is small
python package was written to compute community weighted indices and
specific contributions in their variations.

## Install

_s3c_ requires the following python packages: numpy, pandas, matplotlib.

```bash
# Global install (for all users):
$ sudo pip install -U https://github.com/geeklhem/s3c/zipball/master 
# Local install (for the current user only, do not need root privileges):
$ pip install --user -U https://github.com/geeklhem/s3c/zipball/master
# To uninstall 
$ sudo pip uninstall s3c
``` 

## Tutorial

Quick-start: 

```python
# Provided census and species are well formatted pandas DataFrames.
import s3c
out = s3c.cwi(census, species)
>>> {'cwm': 50.751824869437755, 'cwv': 2423988.1655900856}
``` 

A full tutorial is available in the doc/ folder as an ipython notebook. You
can consult a [static version online](http://nbviewer.ipython.org/github/geeklhem/s3c/blob/master/doc/tutorial.ipynb).


